      "name": "Fresh blueberries",
      "amount": "50g"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat. Add cashews and toast until golden, about 3-4 minutes. Remove and set aside.",
    "In the same pan, add almond milk, coconut cream, maple syrup, and vanilla bean seeds. Warm gently, stirring until syrupy, 3 minutes.",
    "Stir in almond butter, cinnamon, and a pinch of salt until smooth.",
    "Transfer mixture to a bowl, top with toasted cashews.",
    "Add chia seeds, letting them sit for 1 minute to absorb.\n",
    "Spoon fresh blueberries over the top.",
    "Let sit for 5 minutes to allow flavors to meld.",
    "Serve immediately, or chill in the fridge for 30 minutes if preferred.",
    "Enjoy this creamy post-workout bowl."
  ],
